## Key design decisions

**Quiet hours** — store a `quiet_from` / `quiet_to` per user in UTC. Buffer non-urgent notifications (weekly digest, follow-up emails) and release them after the quiet window ends. Never suppress critical alerts (KYC, fraud).

**Priority tiers** — three tiers: `CRITICAL` (always sends, all channels), `REALTIME` (respects quiet hours, sends push + WA), `DIGEST` (batched, email only). Assign per event type.

**Template versioning** — store templates in S3 with a version key. The service resolves the current version at render time, so you can A/B test or roll back without a deployment.

**Broadcaster vs viewer routing** — the same Kafka event may need to notify both the broadcaster (tip received) and a viewer (favourite is live). The notification service holds this fan-out logic, not the originating service.

